    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-chilli-con-carne-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>sweet pointed</strong> <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-chilli-con-carne-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> pepper strips</strong> and<strong> chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-chilli-con-carne-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-chilli-con-carne-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and pepper have softened, increase the heat to high and add your <strong>mince</strong> with your <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (cooking for kids? Skip the chilli!)</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the mince is browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-chilli-con-carne-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince is browned, add the<strong> tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> with the<strong> drained black beans</strong> and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min further or until the sauce is thickened to a bolognese-like consistency and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli con carne</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-chilli-con-carne-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Fluff the <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice</strong> with a fork</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-chilli-con-carne-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chilli con carne </strong>over the<strong> basmati rice</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong>, a dollop of <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Loved this recipe? Keep an eye out for it on the Everyday Favourites section of our menu.</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
